n','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzRmOTgzNmUtMjUwNi00MTc2LTgxZGItNTEyNjM5ZTJhMzQyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyOTIxNDQ1MTQ@._V1_SX300.jpg','Se-Ha (Shin Ha-Kyun) and Dong-Goo (Lee Kwang-Soo) are not blood-related brothers, but they have been like brothers for the past 20 years. Se-Ha is smart, but he has a physical disability. Dong-Goo is not very smart, but he is in excellent physical condition. Mi-Hyun (Esom) is the only person who treats them without prejudice, and she helps them get out into the world.'),(817,'Gordon Lightfoot: If You Could Read My Mind','[\"Gordon Lightfoot\", \" Kim Lightfoot\", \" Bernie Fiedler\"]','Martha Kehoe, Joan Tosoni','Martha Kehoe, Joan Tosoni',7.7,'[\"Documentary\", \" Biography\", \" Music\"]','2020-07-29','91 min','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYWZiMWQwYTEtYjFkZi00MTRkLTg1YmQtZmViMzNhZDA2NzFhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMDc2NTEzMw@@._V1_SX300.jpg','In Canada\'s history, there are few people who signified the nation\'s modern confidence in its arts more than Gordon Lightfoot. This singer-songwriter\'s singular talent in music changed the world\'s opinion of Canada\'s culture with his tremendous variety of songs that both celebrated the nation and touched its soul. Sparing nothing about Lightfoot\'s personal weaknesses and failures as well as his triumphs, this film covers Lightfoot\'s career from his own words and his closest associates with recordings of his greatest hits.'),(818,'In search of the Orient-Express','[\"Charles Berling\", \" Malena Perrot\"]','Louis-Pascal Couvelaire','Louis-Pascal Couvelaire, Marc Eisenchteter',7.3,'[\"Documentary\"]','2019-03-16','86 min','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMThmNTAwZTktYzJjYy00ZWU1LTk1MjMtYzI0YmUyMGZiYzRjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTExODc3ODQ3._V1_SX300.jpg','The mystics and adventure of the legendary Orient Express. Opening in 1883, and closing in 1977, this is the true story, and what is done to save it.'),(819,'Kidnapped by a Classmate','[\"Andrea Bogart\", \" Paige Searcy\", \" Lucas Adams